Combine cornstarch (maizena) and baking powder and add them to the dough as well.
Add almond flour and wheat flour, mix well.
Line a bread pan with parchment paper, sprinkle 2 tablespoons of sugar on the bottom of the pan and spread pear slices over the sugar.
Spoon half of the dough over the pear slices and the apple slices over the dough.
Spoon the rest of the dough over the apple slices.
Cook in the oven at 180 degrees for about an hour until the surface is beautifully browned.
