Young people who socialized early, partyed, sought out good-looking groups, and sought favor with others had an increased risk of substance abuse and crime as young adults.
In their relationships, they fared worse than their once more inconspicuous peers.
Luxury cars, designer bags or watches that communicate high status do not make a person cool - or at least not genuinely attractive company.
